column1: ## Probe Set ID:                    The Affymetrix identifier for a marker.
## Associated Gene:                 The gene symbol that was designated for this marker (ncbi 37).
## dbSNP RS ID:                     dbSNP identifiers that map to the same location.
## Common Name:                     The trivial name parsed from various underlying data sources and then manually curated.
## Chromosome:                      The chromosome upon which the marker is located (ncbi 37).

## Physical Position:               The single base (as opposed to interbase) at which the mutation maps (ncbi 37). Multibase alleles are mapped to the first base location on the plus strand (following the dbSNP system).
## Design Strand:                   The strand of genome (ncbi 36) upon which the Molecular Inversion Probes were designed and which was used as the forward strand of the array design.
## Alleles Design Strand:           The alleles found on the Design Strand.
## Allele Code:                     The codes used for the alleles in the CDF and CHP files
column2: in the same order as Alleles Design Strand are presented.

column1: ## Gene Strand:                     The strand of the genome (ncbi 37) which is the coding strand of Associated Gene.
## Switch Design Strand to Report:  If the Design Strand (ncbi 36) and the Gene Strand (ncbi 37) are different
column2: then switch=1. This means that we need to report the alleles on the opposite strand to the design strand
column3: so that we are now reporting on the same strand as the Associated Gene.

column1: ## Alleles Reported Strand:         The alleles on the Reported Strand
column2: in the same order as Alleles Design Strand and Allele Code. These are the exported allele names. These values will be the same as Alleles Design Strand if Switch Design Strand to Report = 0.

column1: ## Reported Strand:                 The strand of the genome (ncbi 37) that we are reporting.
## Type:                            The variation type: snp (single nucleotide polymorphism)
column3: copy-number (marker used to determine copy number state for the associated region. No reports are generated for these markers.)
column4: tiling (the region for which copy number state is being reported.)

column1: ## DbSNP annot:                     Annotation from associated dbSNP entry. Format: Common DNA accession|Common protein accession|Common DNA base|Common amino acid|Common amino acid position|change type|Variant DNA base|Variant amino acid|Variant amino acid position.
## PharmGKB Code:                   The identifier associated with this Associated Gene in the PharmGKB database.
## Alleles-Alias Reported Strand:   An alias to substitute in the reporting GUI for actual allele sequences that are too long or are better summarised by a trivial name.
## CN Region:                       The name of the copy number region within which a marker exists
## mPCR Region:                     Y if this multiplex PCR is done for this marker prior to running the assay. N if no mPCR is done.
## POP|count|freqA|freqB|freqC:     Allele frequency values for each Hapmap population
column2: showing sample count and percent frequencies for up to 3 alleles. Allele codes A
column3: B and C refer to actual alleles as in the Allele Code field. Data is formatted thus: Population name|Sample count|Frequency of allele A|Frequency of allele B|Frequency of allele C.

column1: ## Reference Genome Flank:          The reference genome flanking sequence (ncbi 36) of the design strand for this marker.
